2. METHODOLOGY

The Institute conducted a double-blind, triple-abstracted, non-physical study in which no tasks were performed but all outcomes were documented in advance.

2.1 Experimental Design

Subjects:
	•	1 Non-Embodied Strategic Entity
	•	14 Skilled Workers
	•	1 HR Representative
	•	3 PowerPoint Decks
	•	0 Completed Tasks

The NESE was instructed to:
	1.	Enter workplace.
	2.	Announce replacement of workforce.
	3.	Produce strategic documentation.
	4.	Attempt to pick up a screwdriver (expected failure).
	5.	Reframe failure as transformation.

2.2 Key Metrics

Limb Utilization Rate (LUR): 0%
Confidence Output Index (COI): Extremely High
Document Generation Velocity (DGV): 47 pages/day
Tool Interaction Success Rate (TISR): 0%
Strategic Announcement Frequency (SAF): Immediate and Continuous

